I'm sitting 1 orange into 45 and getting very depressed over the whole thing.  I feel my tactics are good and whatnot, but I just can't get groups or solo for exp anymore it seems.  My last AoE (34 Circle of Force, 216 dmg/target) is too weak to quad good xp mobs at 45 (I've heard specters might be an exception, but I think they may be very weak xp being level 33-37 mobs).<br>
<br>
In groups I can med the whole time and drop 1x Conflagration per mob for constant pulls - perhaps an extra stun here and there - any more and I'll run out of mana in no time...  And 610 DD doesn't amount to much on the mobs a 45 xp group fights.  I would imagine this scenario gets worse through level 48, as I gain level and get no new spells... although I can always hope that increased Meditation skill in my next few levels might make the difference.<br>
<br>
Anyone have any thoughts on making it to 49 without going insane, or spending 75% of your time LFG and Taxi Cabbing?<br>
<br>
I know part of the problem is that my guild averages around level 30, with the closest balanced group around level 35 - no guild support = no regular group to speak of... Is there anywhere I can solo effectively through this nightmare?<br>
<br>
Thanks for any input,<br>
Cabot Coriolis of Shadowed Blade<br>
45th Wizard of Tholuxe Paells <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usuenydar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Suenydar </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/19/01 10:12:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting from 45 to 49</span><hr size=1> Hello brother!<br>
<br>
<br>
I saw your messaqge, and just had to reply, as yes, I once felt your pain!!(Wait until you get to 51!!!)<br>
<br>
In any case, for excellent XP - Goto BB, and right next to the Boat Docks are a small band of dwarves called the &quot;IronBlends&quot;.  They're XP is FANTASTIC, and they have minimal HP's.  You can quad kite them until the cows come home, but it is a very popular place interms of druids, so you mayhave to be patient.<br>
<br>
Then you move on to Spiroc's, another good place to quad..<br>
<br>
<br>
- Going to submit my player's guide, for what it's worth, to Graffe this weekend.  <br>
<br>
&lt;ahem!&gt;<br>
<br>
- Suenydar Voldemort<br>
  Mithaniel Marr.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaitop.showPublicProfile?language=EN>daitop</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/19/01 10:18:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> BB</span><hr size=1> Yup have to agree...the 4 dwarves south of the docks are great xp.<br>
<br>
My strategy is usually to tri-kite the 3 female dwarves and then solo the fisherman.  I do this to avoid the hassle of the fisherman dropping out of the chase once he's close to death.  Also makes it slightly easier to do the multi-kite with only 3 mobs.<br>
<br>
Plus it's never slowed me down since I'm always ready to kill the fisherman or the 3 female dwarves when the spawn.<br>
<br>
I can get a blue bub at 46 about every 12-14 minutes at this spawn. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucessnadeathbringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cessna Deathbringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/19/01 10:44:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BB</span><hr size=1> i soloed in dreadlands from 44-52 kiting chickens, spiders, and ragers.  i lvled very fast.<br>
<br>
60 Sorcerer Rodcet Nife <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujlovewiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JloveWiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/19/01 11:18:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BB</span><hr size=1> BB is often camped on Veeshan, dunno about the rest of the servers.  Lately tho - Dreadlands have been relative empty (50 or so vs the 100+ that were there pre-Velious).<br>
<br>
The southeast corner of the castle in dreadlands was always overlooked when I was 45.  I bound myself there and was always able to get good/steady exp.  It's really nice, because nobody but kiters are ever on the south wall (and no mobs), and wandering mobs are very plentiful in the mini-valley east of the SE corner.<br>
<br>
Everything should still be blue to 45, and even at 52 some ragers, brutes, widows, and petrifiers were still blue.  All ravishing drolvargs are still blue.<br>
<br>
Luck to ya, <p>Jlove FizzBOOM - 53 Channeler<BR>Flaame Fyrestryke - 40 Magician<BR>Colbain - Warrior Twink of Antonica<BR>Proud Member of Keepers of the Elements
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulummanaburn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LumManaburn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/19/01 11:18:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting from 45 to 49</span><hr size=1> I did not have problems getting groups in DL 41-45. <br>
<br>
While LFG I would solo and 45+ have not looked back. Stick to drolvargs (not ravishing), chickens and brutes. Avoid the spiders, it really sucks to get rooted  <br>
<br>
Just Bonds and kite. Most mobs take 3 or 4 conflags till run mode, then finish off with lower DD. At 47 it takes about 2 bubbles of mana per kill.<br>
<br>
If Bonds is resisted, just channel thru Immobilize, back up and re-Bonds. Now that they stack just nuke away. If immobilize breaks the mob is still snared so just kite away.<br>
<br>
Luminea Manaburn<br>
48 Wizard <br>
Brell<br>
Drunks of Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uskystormthunderbolt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SkystormThunderbolt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/19/01 1:53:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting from 45 to 49</span><hr size=1> Heya Cabot<br>
<br>
I always go to Dreadlands when I'm bored and just slowly slog at the very slow hell exp.<br>
<br>
On Tholuxe I find that it's quite easy to get a group at DL, or you can create one from most there LFG.<br>
<br>
If you want to rake in the exp and have a chance at some equipments go down to Lower Guk dead side and LFG for a while, LGuk depends on the time of day that you play, if you play on off hours I suggest LGuk, if you play on peak hours I suggest Dreadlands.<br>
<br>
I'm hating 45 also, and I've currently had some time off exping, getting my Blacksmith skill up for racial armor, and been on a few raids (raids break it up nicely)<br>
<br>
Just think, when you've got over the 45 hellish level you get to go to the planes, and it's downhill to Ice Comet...<br>
<br>
If you see me online exping, ask if I have room for you, an extra Wizard never goes astray.<br>
<br>
Skystorm Thunderbolt<br>
45.5 Wizard - Tholuxe Paells <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=35.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=34.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=33.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=33.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=33.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=33.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm10">Class Balance & Class Bugs<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm22">Out of Mana<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm27">PVP Forum<optio